currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: You have the opportunity to interpret the words as you like.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You have the opportunity to interpret the words as you like.

currentSuggestions.original: However, in my opinion, there really is no bad way to get your book read.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: However, in my opinion, there really is no bad way to get your book read.

currentSuggestions.original: It is more of an event.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It is more of an event.

currentSuggestions.original: Also, reading a book is somewhat like immersing oneself in the world of the author.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Also, reading a book is somewhat like immersing oneself in the world of the author.

currentSuggestions.original: Listening to audio books is good, but reading a book gives you a chance to think about the text and make all the connections.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Listening to audio books is good, but reading a book gives you a chance to think about the text and make all the connections.

ops.insert: Also, reading a book is somewhat like immersing oneself in the world of the author.

currentSuggestions.original: Young children may especially benefit from listening to the reading of a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Young children may especially benefit from listening to the reading of a book.

currentSuggestions.original: For example, I have read several Poe stories by listening to them.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: For example, I have read several Poe stories by listening to them.

currentSuggestions.original: Like in some languages, hearing the way something is said might be more clear than reading it.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Like in some languages, hearing the way something is said might be more clear than reading it.

currentSuggestions.original: Everyone's voices are different.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Everyone's voices are different.

currentSuggestions.original: As for reading being better than listening, I don't think there is a clear answer.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: As for reading being better than listening, I don't think there is a clear answer.

currentSuggestions.original: I am currently listening to a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I am currently listening to a book.

currentSuggestions.original: But I must say, the experience of the written word is superior.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: But I must say, the experience of the written word is superior.

currentSuggestions.original: I did like your choice of book to interview though.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I did like your choice of book to interview though.

currentSuggestions.original: Like listening to your favourite song.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Like listening to your favourite song.

currentSuggestions.original: That is not the same experience as a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: That is not the same experience as a book.

currentSuggestions.original: I don't dismiss audiobooks completely though.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I don't dismiss audiobooks completely though.

currentSuggestions.original: To listen, you can only focus on what is being said.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: To listen, you can only focus on what is being said.

currentSuggestions.original: And of course, there are other benefits like listening to them in the car.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: And of course, there are other benefits like listening to them in the car.

currentSuggestions.original: As for why we read in the first place, there are many reasons.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: As for why we read in the first place, there are many reasons.

currentSuggestions.original: Edit: Having listened to the author's radio interviews, I now understand there is a bit of irony in my answer.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Edit: Having listened to the author's radio interviews, I now understand there is a bit of irony in my answer.

currentSuggestions.original: Do you agree with me?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Do you agree with me?

currentSuggestions.original: I believe you need to put your full attention into it.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I believe you need to put your full attention into it.

currentSuggestions.original: We do sometimes listen to audiobooks while driving, but other than that we almost always read.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We do sometimes listen to audiobooks while driving, but other than that we almost always read.

ops.insert: I believe you need to put your full attention into it.

currentSuggestions.original: In my opinion, much of reading is in the imagination.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In my opinion, much of reading is in the imagination.

currentSuggestions.original: I believe they are a boon to the visually impaired...
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I believe they are a boon to the visually impaired...

currentSuggestions.original: We should support them for that reason.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We should support them for that reason.

currentSuggestions.original: It is just fine for these people.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It is just fine for these people.

ops.insert: We should support them for that reason.

currentSuggestions.original: Since listening is a division of thoughts and reading the opposite, I believe people should read if they have the time and interest.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Since listening is a division of thoughts and reading the opposite, I believe people should read if they have the time and interest.

currentSuggestions.original: Many of the rare and out of print books have been converted to audio format.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Many of the rare and out of print books have been converted to audio format.

currentSuggestions.original: Therefore, I think audiobooks are great and should be supported however one wants to interpret it.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Therefore, I think audiobooks are great and should be supported however one wants to interpret it.

currentSuggestions.original: Sometimes I think our society has only two choices for us if we have a disability.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Sometimes I think our society has only two choices for us if we have a disability.
